  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The result is as expected:\r\n\r\n```\r\nWithout quote: []\r\nSingle quoted: [ hello.txt]\r\nDouble quoted: [‘hello’.txt]\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo show context (VS Code, using https://github.com/PowerShell/EditorSyntax/pull/156) :\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26179051/60039895-6587fc80-967d-11e9-95da-56501b028473.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26179051/60040155-f068f700-967d-11e9-836a-fa437dee3c50.png)\r\n\r\nThe fancy quotes (``` `u{2018}-`u{201B} ```) will require doubling them to escape them if they are to be contained in a single quoted string.  This is the same as a single `'` when used in a file name.\r\n\r\n",
